<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The constructor for Zend_Auth_Result contains:</p>

<pre><code>    if ($code &lt; self::FAILURE_UNCATEGORIZED) {
        $code = self::FAILURE;
    } ...
</code></pre>

<p>where:</p>

<pre><code>const FAILURE_UNCATEGORIZED          = -4;
</code></pre>

<p>This makes it impossible to create subclasses of this with custom results while still using the parent constructor for future proofing as any result with a lesser value for $code will have it reset to -4.</p>

<p>Suggested fix would be to make FAILURE_UNCATEGORIZED arbitrarily low - such as -9999.</p>

    </div>
